Police are looking for a man who left a loaded gun and a motorcycle outside a company in Industrial Area. According to witnesses, the man had spent more than three hours a few metres from the entrance of Mega Spin Limited, a textiles firm on Stanely Mathenge Road. Simon Ouma, a boda boda operator, said they thought the man, who had partially covered his face, was also a boda boda operator. ALSO READ:

Nakuru residents pleased by rehabilitation of infrastructure “The man appeared to be waiting for a client, but we got concerned over his prolonged staring at the premises,” said Mr Ouma. Security guards manning the company’s entrance alerted police officers on patrol about the man. Nakuru OCPD Samuel Obara said the man took to his heels when he spotted the officers, leaving the items behind.